<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="18.[707,1194,263,1347]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,845,449,470]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named for the collector of the 
<typeStatus box="[835,918,476,497]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">holotype</typeStatus>
and world renowned insect specialist, Albert E. Brookes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="18.[707,1194,263,1347]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,836,529,550]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from the other species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Broun, 1893 b:" authorityYear="1050" box="[1028,1101,556,577]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Sagola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtalis">
<emphasis box="[1028,1101,556,577]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">hirtalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
speciesgroup by the following combination of characters: smaller body size, 
<quantity box="[897,977,609,630]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
; antennomere 1 elongate, approximately 2 times longer than wide; antennomeres 2–10 subquadrate; posterior frontal fovea oval; eye large, one-half length of temple; hind wings reduced to small pads; mid-tibia bent; shape of genitalia unique to species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[707,1194,263,1347]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,941,768,789]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Description of Male.</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity box="[1039,1124,768,789]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
. Body brown, elytra, legs, and maxillary palpi paler (
<figureCitation box="[714,789,821,842]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[197,229,1638,1657]" captionTargetBox="[190,1185,642,1617]" captionTargetId="figure-178@8.[173,1193,624,1622]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Habitus of Sagola species in the hirtalis species-group, dorsal views. a) Sagola hirtalis, b) S. terricola, c) S. convexa, d) S. coromandelensis, e) S. northlandensis, f) S. taranakiensis, g) S. kuscheli, h) S. newtoni, i) S. thorpei, j) S. dugdalei, k) S. thayerae, l) S. hunuaensis, m) S. waikatoensis, n) S. gisbornensis, o) S. weiri, p) S. brookesi. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907747" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907747/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 3p</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,872,821,842]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Head:</emphasis>
As long as wide, widest across eyes (
<figureCitation box="[770,850,848,869]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[197,229,1638,1657]" captionTargetBox="[190,1185,642,1617]" captionTargetId="figure-178@8.[173,1193,624,1622]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Habitus of Sagola species in the hirtalis species-group, dorsal views. a) Sagola hirtalis, b) S. terricola, c) S. convexa, d) S. coromandelensis, e) S. northlandensis, f) S. taranakiensis, g) S. kuscheli, h) S. newtoni, i) S. thorpei, j) S. dugdalei, k) S. thayerae, l) S. hunuaensis, m) S. waikatoensis, n) S. gisbornensis, o) S. weiri, p) S. brookesi. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907747" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907747/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 3p</figureCitation>
). Antennomere 1 approximately 2 times longer than wide, 2–10 subquadrate. Frontal sulcus deep and reaching hind point of eye from end of frontal rostral lobes. Anterior frontal fovea oval, posterior frontal fovea oval. Eye large and prominent, one-half length of temple. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[792,878,1007,1028]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Thorax:</emphasis>
Prosternum as long as wide, widest at one-third length. Elytra rectangular (
<figureCitation box="[714,791,1060,1081]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[197,229,1638,1657]" captionTargetBox="[190,1185,642,1617]" captionTargetId="figure-178@8.[173,1193,624,1622]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Habitus of Sagola species in the hirtalis species-group, dorsal views. a) Sagola hirtalis, b) S. terricola, c) S. convexa, d) S. coromandelensis, e) S. northlandensis, f) S. taranakiensis, g) S. kuscheli, h) S. newtoni, i) S. thorpei, j) S. dugdalei, k) S. thayerae, l) S. hunuaensis, m) S. waikatoensis, n) S. gisbornensis, o) S. weiri, p) S. brookesi. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907747" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907747/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 3p</figureCitation>
). Hind wings absent. Meso- and metathorax trapezoidal, as long as wide. Mid-tibia bent. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[766,878,1113,1134]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Abdomen:</emphasis>
Tergite IV without patches of microtrichia. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[837,944,1140,1161]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Aedeagus:</emphasis>
Median lobe longer than parameres. Phallobase of median lobe asymmetrical and triangular (
<figureCitation box="[889,962,1193,1214]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[175,207,1144,1163]" captionTargetBox="[166,1166,194,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-247@9.[151,1171,183,1135]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Sagola species in the hirtalis species-group. Aedeagi, dorsal view: a) S. hirtalis, b) S. terricola, c) S. convexa, d) S. coromandelensis, e) S. northlandensis, f) S. taranakiensis, g) S. kuscheli, h) S. newtoni, i) S. thorpei, j) S. dugdalei, k) S. thayerae, l) S. hunuaensis, m) S. waikatoensis, n) S. gisbornensis, o) S. weiri, p) S. brookesi. S. hirtalis: q) Antenna, r) Head, dorsal view, s) Head, ventral view (arrow indicates transverse depression). S. terricola: t) Meso- and metaventrite, u) Male fore femur (arrow indicates semicircular depression). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907749" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907749/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 4p</figureCitation>
). Left paramere divided into 2 branches from base and minor branch long and bent (
<figureCitation box="[807,882,1246,1267]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[175,207,1144,1163]" captionTargetBox="[166,1166,194,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-247@9.[151,1171,183,1135]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Sagola species in the hirtalis species-group. Aedeagi, dorsal view: a) S. hirtalis, b) S. terricola, c) S. convexa, d) S. coromandelensis, e) S. northlandensis, f) S. taranakiensis, g) S. kuscheli, h) S. newtoni, i) S. thorpei, j) S. dugdalei, k) S. thayerae, l) S. hunuaensis, m) S. waikatoensis, n) S. gisbornensis, o) S. weiri, p) S. brookesi. S. hirtalis: q) Antenna, r) Head, dorsal view, s) Head, ventral view (arrow indicates transverse depression). S. terricola: t) Meso- and metaventrite, u) Male fore femur (arrow indicates semicircular depression). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907749" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907749/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 4p</figureCitation>
). Right paramere L-shaped and as long as left (
<figureCitation box="[855,928,1273,1294]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[175,207,1144,1163]" captionTargetBox="[166,1166,194,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-247@9.[151,1171,183,1135]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Sagola species in the hirtalis species-group. Aedeagi, dorsal view: a) S. hirtalis, b) S. terricola, c) S. convexa, d) S. coromandelensis, e) S. northlandensis, f) S. taranakiensis, g) S. kuscheli, h) S. newtoni, i) S. thorpei, j) S. dugdalei, k) S. thayerae, l) S. hunuaensis, m) S. waikatoensis, n) S. gisbornensis, o) S. weiri, p) S. brookesi. S. hirtalis: q) Antenna, r) Head, dorsal view, s) Head, ventral view (arrow indicates transverse depression). S. terricola: t) Meso- and metaventrite, u) Male fore femur (arrow indicates semicircular depression). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907749" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907749/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 4p</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
